tourBios.carHigh:
Has made 71 Australasian Tour starts during his career and collected 20 top-25 finishes through the 2012 season. Has also competed on the OneAsia Tour in his career.

2015: Played in 21 Web.com Tour events, making 10 cuts. Had two top-25s, a T20 at the Greater Dallas Open and a T23 at the Digital Ally Open. Finished 122nd on the Regular Season money list.

2014: Played in 24 Web.com Tour events, making 10 cuts. Had one top-10 and three top-25s. Finished the Regular Season 63rd on the money list...Recorded career-best Web.com Tour performance in July when he finished T2 at the Utah Championship. Opened with an even-par 71, then set a personal best when he fired a 10-under 61 at Willow Creek CC. Turned in weekend rounds of 69-66 to finish four strokes behind winner Andres Gonzales, along with Sung Kang and Travis Bertoni...Other top-25s both came in late summer, a T17 in Knoxville and a T24 in Kansas City...Missed the cut in all four Web.com Tour Finals.

2013: Made the cut in 17 of 25 starts during his first full Web.com Tour season and had four top-25 finishes. Posted his only top-10 of the campiagn when he finished T6 at the Midwest Classic near Kansas City in July. Fired an 8-under-par 63 in the third round, his low Web.com Tour round...Made the cut in two of four Finals' events, with a T11 at the Hotel Fitness Championship his best week. Fired a 7-under 65 in the final round to move up 20 spots on the final day. 

2008: Turned in his best Web.com Tour performance, a fourth-place showing at the HSBC New Zealand PGA Championship, which was reduced to 36 holes because of heavy rains during tournament week in Christchurch...Also finished T15 at the Moonah Classic in Australia. 

2007: Made only three U.S. starts on the Web.com Tour. Was T30 at The Rex Hospital Open...Added a T44 at the Knoxville Open and missed the cut at the Legend Financial Group Classic.

1997: First began playing on the Australasian Tour.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Played on the Queensland School Boys team in 1991-92...Competed on the Queensland Junior team in 1993.
tourBios.personal: Favorite golf memory was caddying for his father...Biggest thrill in golf was playing with Greg Norman when he was a rookie and Norman was the No. 1-ranked player in the world...Never travels without a XXXX Gold beer koozie...Favorite pro team is the Brisbane Broncos...Twitter account is @thecrawgolf...Would like to trade places for a day with the Australian cricket team captain...Not many people know he used to sleepwalk as a kid and would sometimes wake up a half-mile from home.
